---Storage Gateway---
Allows you to store data on the AWS cloud and still be able to use it with your on-premises software apps and IT environment. 

Donwload as VM image installed on a host in your datacenter. Supports VMware or Microsoft Hyper-V. Once the VM is installed and configured with AWS account info, you can use the AWS management console to create the gateway option you want.

3 types of gateway
    File gateway (NFS & SMB)
        +Stored in S3 buckets
        +Accessed through Network File System (NFS) mount point
    Volume gateway (iSCSI)
        +volumes are stored in EBS snapshots
        +Stored volumes
        +cached volumes
    Tape Gateway (VTL)


